pageContext.claim: “They say that I was doing so much better than they thought that they panicked, and they started just doing ballot after ballot very quickly and just checking the Biden name on top. They didn't have time. So, you have all these ballots with just one name checked. People don't vote that way. People don't vote that way. They want to vote against taxes, and they want to vote for judges, and they want to vote for a lot of other things that you have on the ballot, you know, different -- different races, including Congress. And they were just checked on top. Tremendous numbers of ballots like that.”
pageContext.analysis: There is nothing suspicious about lower participation in lower level races. It happens all the time. Moreover, while Biden received about 100,000 more votes in Georgia than Democratic Senate candidate Jon Ossoff, that does not mean that all of those votes skipped the Senate race; voters could have been ticket-splitting.
